-- RTL, Ringier Axel Springer, Eye Serbia’s TV Pink, Telegraf Says
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-01-20T15:55:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-20/rtl-ringier-axel-springer-eye-serbia-s-tv-pink-telegraf-says.html
RTL Group SA (RTL) ,  Europe  biggest
broadcaster, is in talks to buy a stake in  TV Pink , a Serbian
national broadcaster,  Telegraf  news website reported, citing TV
Pink’s owner.  Other potential buyers of the unspecified stake include
 Ringier Axel Springer Media AG , the joint venture of Europe’s
biggest newspaper publisher and Switzerland-based Ringier AG,
and Mid Europa Partners Ltd. which owns  Serbia  Broadband, or
SBB, the biggest cable provider in Serbia, according to the
report, which cited Zeljko Mitrovic.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  